<db:para>The Methods Example has an additional method in the <db:code>BirthdayParty</db:code> class: <db:code>invite()</db:code>. <db:code>invite()</db:code> is declared with <db:link xlink:href="qobject.xml#Q_INVOKABLE">Q_INVOKABLE</db:link> so that it can be called from QML.</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">    Q_INVOKABLE void invite(const QString &amp;amp;name);
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>In <db:code>example.qml</db:code>, the <db:code>invite()</db:code> method is called in the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtqml-component.xml#completed-signal">Component.onCompleted</db:link> signal handler:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="qml">import QtQuick
import People

BirthdayParty {
    host: Person {
        name: &quot;Bob Jones&quot;
        shoeSize: 12
    }
    guests: [
        Person { name: &quot;Leo Hodges&quot; },
        Person { name: &quot;Jack Smith&quot; },
        Person { name: &quot;Anne Brown&quot; }
    ]

    Component.onCompleted: invite(&quot;William Green&quot;)
}
</db:programlisting>
